      "solution": "n = int(input())\n\ns = 1\nnum = 1\ndebug = False\nadd = n-1\nwhile add>0:\n    for i in range(4 if add > 1 else 3):\n        if debug:\n            print(f\"Adding {add} to {num}, sum is {s}\")\n        num += add\n        s+=num\n    add -= 2\n\nprint(s)",
      "statement": "Given a matrix of shape [[N]]×[[N]] arranged in a \"spiral\", with its numbers spiralling from <<1>> to [[N]]<<²>> inward, what is the sum of its diagonals? See examples to clarify what a spiral is.\n\n<<Example 1:>>\nThe input: 3\nGives the following spiral:\n`<<1>>     2     <<3>> \n8     <<9>>     4\n<<7>>     6     <<5>>`The sum of the diagonals is:\n1 + 3 + 5 + 7 + 9 = 25\n\n\n<<Example 2:>>\nThe input: 4\nGives the following spiral:\n`<<1>>    2      3     <<4>>\n12   <<13>>    <<14>>     5\n11   <<16>>    <<15>>     6\n<<10>>   9      8     <<7>>`The sum of the diagonals is:\n1 + 4 + 7 + 10 + 13 + 14 + 15 + 16 = 80",
